text: Vic Cathedral (, ), officially the Cathedral of St. Peter the Apostle (, ) is a Roman Catholic cathedral in Vic, Catalonia, Spain. It is the seat of the Diocese of Vic. It has a mix of Romanesque, Gothic, Baroque and Neoclassic styles. ==Other websites== Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Spain Category:Buildings and structures in Catalonia Category:10th-century buildings and structures
title: Vic Cathedral
